The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Electrosteel Castings Ltd has reported a 31 per cent rise in its operating profit at Rs 212.67 crore in 2006-07 against Rs 162.11 crore in the previous year. The profit before tax increased 47 per cent to Rs 158.42 crore from Rs 107.87 crore. Overall sales rose 17 per cent at Rs 1,176.21 crore in 2006-07 against Rs 1,003.13 crore in the previous year. The companys exports jumped 34 per cent to Rs 447.05 crore during the year.

 Brahmaputra Consortium Ltd (BCL) has sought market regulator Sebis nod for its IPO. The company plans to issue 4.2 million equity shares of Rs 10 each. The price band will be decided later. BCL has an order book of around Rs 730 crore on January 1, 20007.

 Jaybharat Textiles and Real Estate Ltd has posted a 93.19 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 12.27 crore during the fourth quarter ended March 31 against Rs 6.35 crore in the year-ago period. The net sales increased 58.82 per cent to Rs 82.76 crore from Rs 52.11 crore in the corresponding quarter of the last fiscal.

 KSL Realty and Infrastructure Ltd has posted a 35.78 per cent increase in its net sales at Rs 137.34 crore during the fourth quarter ended March 31 against Rs 101.15 crore in the year-ago period. The EBITDA increased 80 per cent to Rs 34.48 crore from Rs 19.09 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.

 Glory Polyfilms Ltd will enter the capital market on May 9. The IPO is of 822,000 equity shares of Rs 10 each at a premium of Rs 38 per share. The issue comprises 47.06 per cent of the post-issue paid-up capital of the company. The IPO closes on May 15.

 Textile sourcing company Indus Fila has posted a 227 per cent year-on-year increase in its total income for 2006-07 at Rs 273.64 crore against Rs 83.67 crore in the previous fiscal. Profit after tax rose 406 per cent to Rs 26.14 crore from Rs 5.18 crore last year. 

 Mr Bectors Cremica has launched a range of mayonnaise in the city. They will be available in chunky lemon, chunky mint and onion garlic flavours. 

 Tata Motors has expanded its Indigo XL range with the launch of the Indigo XL Classic. The car offers greater comfort and more leg room. The petrol version is priced at Rs 5.35 lakh, while the diesel one has a price tag of Rs 6.15 lakh.

 Spykar has introduced its spring summer collection 2007 in the city. The range is influenced by the 1970s and comprises dresses, jeans, shorts, skirts, tees, junk jewellery, belts, caps and wallets.

